HEADWORD: Rhonchus
<hw>Rhon"chus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Rhonchi</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a snoring, a
croaking.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An adventitious whistling or
snoring sound heard on auscultation of the chest when the air channels
are partially obstructed. By some writers the term <xex>rhonchus</xex>
is used as equivalent to <xex>r⟦acir⟧le</xex> in its widest sense. See
<er>R⟦acir⟧le</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhopalic</ent>⟦br⟧
